  "text": "The etiology of the thromboembolism after surgery is multifactorial [CITATION_1] . Several thromboembolic events caused by vegetation, thrombus and abnormal flow conditions of the prosthesis. Chronic atrial fibrillation and PHV dysfunction increase the risk of thromboembolism. In patients with mitral valve prosthesis, if left atrium is small, patient is in sinus rhythm and cardiac output is normal, the risk of thromboembolism is low.",
